Usage üìñ
Cite references as you normally do in Pandoc and they will be linked üîó and backlinked üîó to the bibliography üìö
[@citekey]
Use [@Citekey]{.csl_field} to arbitrarily üéØü•ã print specific fields instead of the usual Author-Date.
[@citekey]{.author}
[@citekey]{.title}
[@citekey]{.original-title}
Append the field name with a dot (.) to avoid creating a link to the bibliography in this particular citationüìç
[@citekey]{.author.}
This can also be done globally üåê by setting link-fields: false in the metadata3
---
link-fields: false
---

